{"title":"iOS 14.5: You may soon get to choose your default music and podcast apps","link":"https://www.macworld.com/article/3606491/ios-145-you-may-soon-get-to-choose-your-default-music-and-podcast-apps.html#tk.rss_all","date":1612806780000,"content":"<div id=\"readability-page-1\" class=\"page\"><section role=\"main\" id=\"page-wrapper\"><article itemscope=\"\" itemtype=\"http://schema.org/NewsArticle\"><meta itemprop=\"keywords\" content=\"mobile, siri, small and medium business \"><header><ins data-ad-client=\"ca-pub-4268075595326305\" data-ad-slot=\"9945794902\" data-ad-format=\"link\" data-adsbygoogle-status=\"done\"><ins id=\"aswift_1_expand\" tabindex=\"0\" title=\"Advertisement\" aria-label=\"Advertisement\"><ins id=\"aswift_1_anchor\"></ins></ins></ins><section><h3 itemprop=\"description\">Users of the iOS 14.5 beta have found the new feature, which is buggy and still in development.</h3></section><div><p>Staff Writer, <span itemprop=\"publisher\" itemscope=\"\" itemtype=\"http://schema.org/Organization\"><span itemprop=\"name\">Macworld</span><meta itemprop=\"url\" content=\"https://www.macworld.com\"><meta itemprop=\"logo\" content=\"https://alt.idgesg.net/images/furniture/macworld/MW_logo_300x300.png\"></span><span>|</span> <span itemprop=\"datePublished\" content=\"2021-02-08T09:53-0800\"><span>Feb 8, 2021 9:53 am PST</span></span></p></div></header><div><div><figure itemprop=\"image\" itemscope=\"\" itemtype=\"http://schema.org/ImageObject\"><meta itemprop=\"representativeOfPage\" content=\"1\"><meta itemprop=\"height\" content=\"800\"><meta itemprop=\"width\" content=\"1200\"><meta itemprop=\"url\" content=\"https://images.idgesg.net/images/article/2021/02/ios-spotify-default-100876519-large.jpg\"><img data-original=\"https://images.idgesg.net/images/article/2021/02/ios-spotify-default-100876519-large.jpg\" loading=\"lazy\" alt=\"ios spotify default\" itemprop=\"contentUrl\" src=\"https://images.idgesg.net/images/article/2021/02/ios-spotify-default-100876519-large.jpg\"><figcaption kioskedhash_production=\"11429_f0a7297260cdcee4d21cf60a89b592de\" data-kiosked-context-name=\"kskdUIContext_01ey1f7034deptx9b1ds7w7hqm\"><span itemprop=\"copyrightHolder\">IDG</span></figcaption></figure></div></div><section><div id=\"drr-container\" itemprop=\"articleBody\"><p>Users on Reddit may have found an exiting—but unlisted—feature of iOS 14.5. When asking Siri to play a song, artist, album, or podcast, some users have been prompted to select which service they wish to play it on, with a list of the installed music or podcast apps.</p><p>The process is simple, but inconsistent. Just have <a href=\"https://www.macworld.com/article/3605528/ios-14-5-features-release-date-beta-how-to-install.html\">iOS 14.5 beta</a> installed and ask Siri to play a song or artist. Siri will prompt you with a list of available services to choose from. After selecting one, Siri asks if it’s okay to access your data from that app. Agree, and your music or podcast plays on that app. Further requests to play music or podcasts will then automatically play on that app.</p><figure kioskedhash_production=\"11429_77c8cb85d923990ba30cdba9e63e11e2\" data-kiosked-context-name=\"kskdUIContext_01ey1f7034deptx9b1ds7w7hqm\"><a href=\"https://images.idgesg.net/images/article/2021/02/siri-spotify-default02-100876516-orig.jpg\" rel=\"nofollow\" title=\"<div class='credit'>IDG</div>\n<p>Apple is clearly working on the ability to change music and podcast defaults.</p>\n\"><img alt=\"siri spotify default02\" width=\"1200\" height=\"800\" data-imageid=\"100876516\" data-license=\"IDG\" data-original=\"https://images.idgesg.net/images/article/2021/02/siri-spotify-default02-100876516-large.jpg\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://images.idgesg.net/images/article/2021/02/siri-spotify-default02-100876516-large.jpg\"></a><small>IDG</small><figcaption><p>Apple is clearly working on the ability to change music and podcast defaults.</p></figcaption></figure><p>It’s not working for all beta testers, however. Some users have had luck removing the Apple Music app, but reinstalling it seems to often make Siri go back to playing everything on Apple Music or Podcasts. Furthermore, there is no interface for any of this in Settings.</p><p>You can already tell Siri to play music or podcasts using a third-party service by naming the service in your request. For example, “Play The Weeknd on Spotify.” But the power of defaults is enormous, and humans don’t like to constantly direct voice assistants to use non-default services. Clearly, Apple is at least doing some early work to allow users to choose a default music or podcasts app. When, how, or even <em>if</em> it will see public release&nbsp;is unclear at this time.</p><div><p><img onclick=\"jwplayer('bottomRightPlayer').remove(); this.style.display = 'none';\" id=\"jw-standalone-close-button\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\"></p><div id=\"bottomRightPlayer\" tabindex=\"0\" aria-label=\"Video Player\" role=\"application\" aria-describedby=\"jw-shortcuts-tooltip-explanation\"><div dir=\"auto\"><p>Apple Watch 6 vs SE vs 3: Which model is right for your wrist?</p></div><p><span aria-live=\"assertive\"></span><span aria-live=\"assertive\">Volume 0%</span></p></div></div><div><p>Note: When you purchase something after clicking links in our articles, we may earn a small commission. Read our <a href=\"https://www.macworld.com/about/affiliates.html\">affiliate link policy</a> for more details.</p></div></div><div><p>Jason has written professionally about technology for over 20 years. His goal is to figure out how complicated technology works and explain it in a way anyone can understand.</p></div></section></article></section></div>","author":"Jason Cross","siteTitle":"Macworld","siteHash":"37e84dd5a21fa961d6d6630e269546024dbb7741b2e2fadbe74f47383c70dfbb","entryHash":"7c003d9ecbcb59be9aeee02f88e3126aac4096dabf0d05d7cb00ed7a27a529ca","category":"Apple"}